The Honourable Minister of the FCT, Malam Muhammad Musa Bello has offered the heartfelt condolences of the FCT Administration to President Muhammadu Buhari and the entire Kyari family on the passing of the Presidentâ€™s Chief of Staff, Malam Abba Kyari. This was made known in a statement released on Sunday to DAILY POST by the chief Press Secretary, Anthony Ogunleye. Bello described the late Chief of Staff as a quintessential administrator whose great wealth of experience spanning both the public and private sectors was positively brought to bear in the management of the affairs of the country including the FCT. He prayed that Almighty Allah (SWT) grants him eternal rest in Jannatul Firdaus and gives his family the strength to bear the loss. Recall that Kyari on Friday night, after battling the deadly Coronavirus However, his body arrived in Abuja on Saturday where he was buried according to Islamic rites.